Weight loss and control topics

   Each of the topics below exists as a booklet or fact sheet. Copies may
   be ordered from the National Weight-control Information Network (WIN).
     * Active at Any Size
     * Binge Eating Disorder
     * Celebrate the Beauty of Youth
     * Choosing a Safe and Successful Weight-Loss Program
     * Dieting and Gallstones
     * Do You Know the Health Risks of Being Overweight?
     * Energize Yourself and Your Family
     * Fit and Fabulous as You Mature
     * Gastric Surgery for Severe Obesity
     * Helping Your Overweight Child
     * Improving Your Health: Tips for African American Men and Women
     * Nutrition and Your Health: Dietary Guidelines for Americans
     * Physical Activity and Weight Control
     * Prescription Medications for the Treatment of Obesity (revised
       February 2001; Research)
     * Release of Clinical Guidelines To Identify, Evaluate, and Treat
       Overweight and Obesity in Adults
     * Take Charge of Your Health: A Teenager's Guide to Better Health
     * Understanding Adult Obesity
     * Very Low-Calorie Diets
     * Walking...A Step in the Right Direction
     * Weight Cycling
     * Weight-loss and Nutrition Myths
     * Weight Loss for Life
     * You Can Control Your Weight as You Quit Smoking

Research

     * Table summarizing long-term studies of pharmacotherapy for the
       management of obesity.

Statistics

     * Statistics Related to Overweight and Obesity Summary fact sheet on
       the prevalence of overweight in the United States.

Order forms

     * Publications Order Form
       Health professionals, patients, and consumers may order single
       copies of most titles in the Publications Titles list free of
       charge. Health professionals may order bulk quantities for a fee.
     * Video Order Form
       The Clinical Nutrition and Obesity Lecture Series videos are a tool
       for health professionals and the public to better understand
       various nutrition and nutrition-related disorders.

